The paper deals with the problem of finding branch-decompositions of various combinatorial objects such as matroids, hypergraphs, and graphs. This falls under the area of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also uses tools from computational geometry (cs.CG) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) to develop their fixed-parameter algorithm. The paper also mentions the use of monadic second-order formulas (cs.DL) and the study of systems and control theory (cs.SY) in related work.
